  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ITmfTimePreferencesConstants  
    ITmfTimestamp
    The fundamental time reference in the TMF.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    TmfNanoTimestamp
    A simplified timestamp where scale is nanoseconds and precision is set to 0.
    TmfSimpleTimestamp
    A simplified timestamp where scale and precision are set to 0.
    TmfTimePreferences
    TMF Time format preferences
    TmfTimeRange
    A utility class to define and manage time ranges.
    TmfTimestamp
    A generic timestamp implementation.
    TmfTimestampDelta
    A generic timestamp implementation for delta between timestamps.
    TmfTimestampFormat
    A formatting and parsing facility that can handle timestamps that span the epoch with a precision down to the nanosecond.
